# <type>(<scope>): <description>
#
# Guidelines for the header:
# - <type>: Commit type, e.g., feat, fix, docs, chore, refactor, deps, test, security, etc.
#   Breaking change: ! before the colon, after the closing paren if scope is present.
#   With scope:    type(scope)!: ...
#   Without scope: type!: ...
# - <scope>: Optional. The specific module, feature, or area affected.
# - <description>: Short, imperative summary. Target ≤60 chars, hard cap 72. No trailing period.
#
# Example: feat(auth): add OAuth login support
#
# Style notes (body renders as plain text in `git log`, VS Code timeline, and most
# GitHub views — only PR bodies render markdown):
# - No backticks, no bold, no italics. Backticks only for regex or quoted string literals.
# - One fact per bullet. Parentheticals inside a bullet: ≤6 words.
# - Blank line before and after every [SECTION] header.
# - If any bullet in a section wraps past one line, blank-line-separate every bullet in it.
# - Prose blocks ([PURPOSE], [IMPACT], detailed description): max 2 sentences;
#   past that, convert to bullets.

<type>(<scope>): <description>

# Detailed description (rare):
# - Use only for breaking-change migration narrative or cross-cutting context that
#   structured sections cannot carry. Default: omit.

<detailed description>

# Changes:
# - Include when the commit covers 3+ logically distinct changes.
# - Logical ≠ mechanical: renaming 5 files is one logical change.

[CHANGES]
 - <list of changes>

# Purpose:
# - State the triggering cause, not the aspiration.
# - Skip when the reason is self-evident from the header.

[PURPOSE]
 - <reason for the change>

# Impact:
# - Observable or actionable effects only. Skip for invisible internal refactors.
# - Must not restate [PURPOSE].

[IMPACT]
 - <description of the impact>

# Affected files:
# - Include deliberate additions and deletions so intent is visible without running git show.
# - [FILES MODIFIED] is not used — `git show --stat` already reports that.
# - Bare file list preferred; add " — role" only when a file's contribution is not
#   inferable from [CHANGES] or header.

[FILES ADDED]
 - <list of files>

[FILES REMOVED]
 - <list of files>

# Dependencies:
# - Only for actual dependency file changes.
# - Formats:
#     ADDED:   - name: version            (e.g. - ruff-pre-commit: v0.15.11)
#     UPDATED: - name: old → new          (e.g. - ruff: ^0.11.12 → ^0.15.11)
#     REMOVED: - name: last-known-version (e.g. - pyupgrade: ^3.15)
# - When >5 entries in one ecosystem: list 2-3 meaningful bumps individually, then
#   "- plus X, Y, Z to latest" for the rest.
# - Separate poetry deps from pre-commit hook revs into different sections if both present.

[DEPENDENCIES ADDED]
 - <list of dependencies>

[DEPENDENCIES UPDATED]
 - <list of dependencies>

[DEPENDENCIES REMOVED]
 - <list of dependencies>

# References:
# - Links to related docs, designs, reviews, external issues.

[REFERENCES]
 - <links to resources>

# Footers (must be last — nothing after these lines):
# - Closes #<n>: one per line. GitHub auto-closes the issue.
# - Refs #<n>:   one per line. Mention without closing.
# - BREAKING CHANGE: must pair with ! in header; must be the final footer.

Closes #<issue-number>

Refs #<issue-number>

# BREAKING CHANGE: <description of breaking changes and required adaptations>
